"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619993","Department of Health","false","2016-10-27","<p>The National Health Service is not required to register miscarriages. Hospital Episode Statistics (HES) provide information on the number of miscarriages. The table shows the number of miscarriages from 2010-11 to 2014-15 where there was a hospital admission. Not all miscarriages will require an admission to hospital.</p><p> </p><p>Activity in English National Health Service hospitals and English NHS commissioned activity in the independent sector</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of miscarriages</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>43,005</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>42,538</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>39,800</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>38,869</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>38,377</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Source</em>: HES, NHS Digital</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-27T14:33:06.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619993/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619993/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-24","Miscarriage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many miscarriages the NHS has registered in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","50041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619994","Department of Health","false","2016-10-27","<p>The best treatment for knee pain will vary depending on the individual and their underlying problem. Patients considering a knee operation should also be given information about alternative treatments such as physiotherapy. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has published clinical guidance on the care and management of osteoarthritis, including knee surgery at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg177" target="_blank">https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg177</a></p><p> </p><p>Clinical commissioning groups are responsible for commissioning services to meet the requirements of their local population. It would be for them to decide whether this procedure should be made available, taking into account any available evidence of its clinical and cost effectiveness.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-27T14:13:04.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619994/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619994/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-24","Orthopaedics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans to make available on the NHS knee injection treatment to replace knee surgery.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","50042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619995","Department of Health","false","2016-10-27","<p>We understand that clinical research is ongoing into the effectiveness of neuroprotective agents in minimising the effects of conditions causing neurodegeneration such as traumatic brain injuries, strokes, and dementia.</p><p> </p><p>The Government and the National Health Service supports research into new technologies through the National Institute for Health Research and its clinical research networks.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2016-10-27T10:10:48.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619995/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619995/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-24","Strokes: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans to make available on the NHS high-tech neuro-protective medication for stroke patients.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","50043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619996","Department of Health","false","2016-10-27","<p>From 31 July 2016 all providers of National Health Service care and publicly funded adult social care have been required to meet the Accessible Information Standard, published by NHS England.</p><p>This requires all organisations to:</p><p>- Ask people if they have any information or communication needs;</p><p>- Record those needs clearly and in a set way;</p><p>- Highlight or flag the person’s file or notes so it is clear that they have information or communication needs and how their needs should be met;</p><p>- Share information about people’s information and communication needs with other providers of NHS and adult social care, when they have consent or permission to do so; and</p><p>- Take steps to ensure that people’s needs are met, including receiving information which they can access and understand, and communication support if they need it. This includes providing information in Braille where identified.</p><p>Further information can be found on NHS England’s website and accessed via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/ourwork/accessibleinfo/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/ourwork/accessibleinfo/</a></p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-27T13:18:57.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619996/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619996/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-24","NHS: Braille","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that NHS services are available to people who read using braille.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","50038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619997","Department of Health","false","2016-10-31","<p>We are aware of recent research regarding a new implant to treat arthritis, however this research remains at a relatively early stage and larger scientific trials would be needed to demonstrate the efficacy and safety of such a device before it could be considered for routine National Health Service use.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-31T16:22:31.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619997/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619997/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-24","Arthritis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans to make the arthritis pacemaker implant available on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","50039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619998","Home Office","false","2016-10-31","<p>The ESOL funding is provided to help refugees learn English and integrate into British society.</p><p>Although it is expected that standards of English will improve, there is currently no standard set attainment level, as ability levels will differ. The ESOL courses should be at least 12 hours a week, for a 3 – 6 month period.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","49967","2016-10-31T17:10:08.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619998/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619998/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the £10 million package announced on 4 September 2016 for resettled Syrian refugees, how many hours of additional English language teaching per refugee that funding will provide.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","49968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619999","Home Office","false","2016-10-31","<p>The ESOL funding is provided to help refugees learn English and integrate into British society.</p><p>Although it is expected that standards of English will improve, there is currently no standard set attainment level, as ability levels will differ. The ESOL courses should be at least 12 hours a week, for a 3 – 6 month period.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","49968","2016-10-31T17:10:08.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619999/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/619999/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the £10 million funding package for English language tuition for resettled Syrian refugees announced on 4 September 2016, how many ESOL levels those eligible to participate will be expected to attain.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","49967"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620000","Home Office","false","2016-11-03","<p>English language tuition forms part of the support package provided to beneficiaries of the Gateway Protection Programme.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-03T17:50:18.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620000/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620000/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Refugees: English Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to provide additional funding for English language tuition for refugees on the Gateway Protection Resettlement Programme.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","50005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620001","Home Office","false","2016-11-11","<p>All those granted refugee status or humanitarian protection become eligible for government skills funding as any other UK resident and are not subject to the normal 3 year qualifying period.</p><p>When someone receives a positive decision on their asylum claim they are provided with relevant information to allow them to access the services they need.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-11T15:41:08.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620001/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620001/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620001/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Refugees: English Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to provide additional funding for English language tuition for refugees who gain settlement rights in the UK under the standard procedure for claiming asylum.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","50006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620002","Home Office","false","2016-10-31","<p>The contract with GEO Ltd to operate Dungavel immigration removal centre (IRC) does not contain a sunset clause. It is extendable for 12 months at a time, until September 2019. It is currently extended to September 2017.</p><p>The closure of Dungavel IRC is dependent on the success of the planning application for the new short term holding facility near Glasgow airport, currently under consideration by Renfrewshire Council.</p><p>The Government announced that it intended to close Dungavel when the new short term holding facility is ready, and therefore it is the Government’s policy to reserve its right to continue to use Dungavel for the purposes of immigration detention should the planning application be unsuccessful.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","49894 ; 49895","2016-10-31T17:24:14.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620002/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620002/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620002/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Dungavel Immigration Removal Centre","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether there is a sunset clause on her Department's use of Dungavel Immigration Removal Centre.","false","Biography information for Carol Monaghan","Glasgow North West","Carol Monaghan","49896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620003","Home Office","false","2016-11-03","<p>Government Ministers and officials receive representations from a wide range of stakeholders. The Prime Minister has been clear that she wants to protect the status of EU nationals here. The only circumstances in which that would not be possible are if British citizens’ rights in other EU Member States were not protected in return.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-03T17:49:14.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620003/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620003/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620003/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","NHS: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent representations she has received from NHS trusts on safeguards for EU nationals working in the NHS after the UK has left the EU; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","49910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620004","Home Office","false","2016-11-03","<p>International students are included in net migration statistics that are produced by the independent Office for National Statistics (ONS). In line with the internationally agreed UN definition, these statistics define a migrant as someone changing their normal place of residence for more than a year. Students are therefore included in the same way as other migrants. Other countries, such as the United States, Canada, and Australia also include students in their net migration figures. Like other migrants, students who stay for longer than 12 months have an impact on communities, infrastructure and services while they are here, so it is right that they are included in the net migration count.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-03T17:50:04.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620004/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620004/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620004/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her Department's policy is on the inclusion of international students as part of the net migration figures; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","49911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620005","Home Office","false","2016-12-21","<p>Unaccompanied asylum seeking children arriving in the UK are transferred to the care of a local authority. The local authority will arrange for the child’s health to be assessed and for a health plan to be drawn up. This will include dental care. Central records are not kept of the number of dental check-ups given to such children.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","49879","2016-12-21T11:02:12.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620005/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620005/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620005/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether it is the Government's policy to ensure that unaccompanied children arriving in the UK to seek asylum are given dental check-ups.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","49880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620006","Home Office","false","2016-10-31","<p>The contract with GEO Ltd to operate Dungavel immigration removal centre (IRC) does not contain a sunset clause. It is extendable for 12 months at a time, until September 2019. It is currently extended to September 2017.</p><p>The closure of Dungavel IRC is dependent on the success of the planning application for the new short term holding facility near Glasgow airport, currently under consideration by Renfrewshire Council.</p><p>The Government announced that it intended to close Dungavel when the new short term holding facility is ready, and therefore it is the Government’s policy to reserve its right to continue to use Dungavel for the purposes of immigration detention should the planning application be unsuccessful.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","49895 ; 49896","2016-10-31T17:24:14.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620006/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620006/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620006/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Dungavel Immigration Removal Centre","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether it is her Department's policy to reserve the right to continue to use Dungavel Immigration Removal Centre in the event that the plan to establish a new detention facility at Glasgow Airport does not go ahead.","false","Biography information for Carol Monaghan","Glasgow North West","Carol Monaghan","49894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620007","Home Office","false","2016-10-31","<p>The contract with GEO Ltd to operate Dungavel immigration removal centre (IRC) does not contain a sunset clause. It is extendable for 12 months at a time, until September 2019. It is currently extended to September 2017.</p><p>The closure of Dungavel IRC is dependent on the success of the planning application for the new short term holding facility near Glasgow airport, currently under consideration by Renfrewshire Council.</p><p>The Government announced that it intended to close Dungavel when the new short term holding facility is ready, and therefore it is the Government’s policy to reserve its right to continue to use Dungavel for the purposes of immigration detention should the planning application be unsuccessful.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","49894 ; 49896","2016-10-31T17:24:14.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620007/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620007/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Dungavel Immigration Removal Centre","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what progress her Department has made on its plans to close Dungavel Immigration Removal Centre and to establish a new detention facility at Glasgow Airport.","false","Biography information for Carol Monaghan","Glasgow North West","Carol Monaghan","49895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620008","Home Office","false","2016-12-21","<p>Unaccompanied asylum seeking children arriving in the UK are transferred to the care of a local authority. The local authority will arrange for the child’s health to be assessed and for a health plan to be drawn up. This will include dental care. Central records are not kept of the number of dental check-ups given to such children.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","49880","2016-12-21T11:02:12.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620008/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620008/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many unaccompanied asylum seeking children arriving in the UK have been given a dental check-up in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","49879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620009","Cabinet Office","false","2016-10-27","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply. What happens in terms of the migration system that will be established as we leave the EU is a matter that will be very closely scrutinised and looked at in great detail by the government and within the government.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2016-10-27T12:48:23.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620009/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620009/answer","Louise Ellman FINAL .pdf","Louise Ellman FINAL .pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Non EU Students","UKSA Letter to Member - Non EU Students","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620009/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-10-24","Immigration: Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of non-EU students who have remained in the UK after completing their studies during the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","49881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620010","Home Office","false","2016-11-01","<p>The Home Secretary’s quarterly report to Parliament on the operation of Terrorism Prevention and Investigation Measure (TPIM) legislation provides some background on current TPIM subjects: the most recent report was published on 26 October 2016 [HCWS220]. Further to the quarterly report we do not comment on the individual circumstances of TPIM subjects past or present.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-11-01T14:07:26.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620010/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620010/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620010/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Terrorism Prevention and Investigation Measures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the letter from the Secretary of State for Defence to the hon. Member for Kingston upon Hull North of 6 June 2016, what information her Department holds on the number of fighters who have returned who (a) are subject to Terrorism Prevention and Investigation Measures (TPIMS), (b) were subject to TPIMs prior to their return and (c) have been prosecuted.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","49882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620011","Home Office","false","2016-10-27","<p>Soliciting remains an offence under section 51A of the Sexual Offences Act 2003, regardless of the sexual orientation of the person who is committing the offence.</p><p>There is a clear distinction drawn between offences which may be eligible for disregard under the Protection of Freedoms Act 2012 and those which relate to behaviour which would still be an offence today.</p><p>There are no plans to extend the set of offences covered by the existing disregard arrangements.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-10-27T16:13:40.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620011/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620011/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Prostitution: Males","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government plans to enable men cautioned for soliciting and importuning under section 32 of the Sexual Offences Act 1956 before 1 May 2004 to have their crimes disregarded.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","49883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620012","Home Office","false","2016-11-07","<p>As the Home Secretary recently announced, we will shortly be consulting on what more we can do to strengthen the system to support the best institutions – and those that stick to the rules – to attract the best talent.</p><p>The consultation will include looking, for the first time, at whether our student immigration rules should be tailored to the quality of the institution.</p><p>Interested parties, including businesses and members of the education sector, will have the opportunity to engage with this consultation to help us get these reforms right.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-07T13:43:00.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620012/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620012/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Overseas Students: Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to review immigration rules for students.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","49924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620013","Home Office","false","2016-11-11","<p>The Government commissioned an independent review of the welfare of vulnerable individuals in detention by Stephen Shaw. We accepted the broad thrust of Mr Shaw’s recommendations, including the adoption of a wider definition of those at risk, and we have strengthened our policies and processes for dealing with the detention of persons who may be vulnerable.</p><p>The Government expect these reforms, and broader changes in legislation, policy and operational approaches, to lead to a reduction in the number of those detained, and the duration of detention before removal, in turn improving the welfare of those detained The immigration detention estate is kept under constant review to make sure we have the right resources in the right places and that we are providing value for money.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-11T15:57:58.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620013/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620013/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620013/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Detention Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to reform the immigration detention estate.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","49925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620014","Home Office","false","2016-11-08","<p>Teams across the Home Office are assessing the impact of the UK’s exit from the EU on their work to establish future requirements</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-08T16:22:35.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620014/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620014/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/620014/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-24","Home Office: Departmental Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the implications of the UK leaving the EU on her departmental responsibilities.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","49926"
