"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/607577","Department for International Trade","false","2016-10-26","<p>The Department for International Trade has already established a strong and capable trade policy team with significant negotiating experience. The team has more than doubled in size since 23 June and is still growing. We will continue to hire the brightest and best talent from within the UK civil service and from elsewhere in order to deliver the best outcomes for the UK.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","49814","2016-10-26T14:16:17.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/607577/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/607577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/607577/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-10-21","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps he is taking to encourage UK nationals with expertise in trade negotiations to return to the UK from other EU countries to act as negotiators.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","49813"
