"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606708","Home Office","false","2016-11-03","<p>On 12 March 2015 the former Home Secretary established the Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse under the Inquiries Act 2005. The Inquiry is independent of the Government and is responsible for the management of its own budget and the publication of its own financial reports.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-03T17:18:23.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606708/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606708/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-20","Child Sexual Abuse Independent Panel Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much has been spent on work by Ben Emmerson QC for the Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse during the period since he left his post as senior lawyer on that inquiry; and if she will publish a breakdown of those costs.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","49569"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606709","Home Office","false","2016-11-01","<p>The Home Office has provided grant funding of £770,500k in this financial year to support the work of Crimestoppers to encourage the public to report information on crime.</p><p>In addition, this year we are also working closely with Crimestoppers to support the re-development of their ‘Fearless’ campaign and website which is targeted at encouraging children and young people to report crime, including through work in schools to raise awareness of the risks and consequences of knife crime.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-01T16:26:23.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606709/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/606709/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-10-20","Crimestoppers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to advertise the independence of Crimestoppers to encourage more people, particularly young people, to come forward with information on crime.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","49586"
